$Id$

To install:

1. Copy the contents of the startup directory to your .jedit/startup
   directory (typically under your home directory).

2. Create a .jedit/macros/Emacs directory.

3. Copy the contents of this directory (i.e., the "bsh" files and
   the shortcut.properties file) to the directory you created in step 2.

4. Fire up JEdit. It should find the Emacs macros and automatically create
   keybindings based on the contents of the shortcut.properties file.

